                <head>2. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On April 27, the National Security Council, in Action No. 1542, directed the
                    Planning Board to undertake an immediate review of those sections of <gloss
                        target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 5409 pertaining to Afghanistan. This review was
                    prompted by the recent Soviet <gloss target="#t_AID1">aid</gloss> agreement with
                    Afghanistan. At its 285th meeting on May 17, the <gloss target="#t_NSC1"
                        >NSC</gloss> discussed the Planning Board’s proposed changes in <gloss
                        target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 5409. For a memorandum of that discussion, see
                        <ref target="#d118">Document 118</ref>.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
